ed":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":248,"license":{"key":"apache-2.0","name":"Apache License 2.0","spdx_id":"Apache-2.0","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/apache-2.0","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTI="},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["assertions","assertj","groovy","hacktoberfest","java","kotlin","testing","typed-assertions"],"visibility":"public","forks":754,"open_issues":248,"watchers":2769,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"## Overview\n\nIn the Spring Framework, I recently introduced a test which needed to [assert both the cause and suppressed exceptions](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/6bbfd56dced92aa8465668ed3a28e740978a042d/spring-core/src/test/java/org/springframework/core/retry/RetryTemplateTests.java#L175-L183) in a given `Throwable`.\n\nThat currently looks something like this.\n\n```java\nassertThatExceptionOfType(RetryException.class)\n\t\t.isThrownBy(() -> retryTemplate.execute(retryable))\n\t\t.withMessage(\"Retry policy for operation 'test' exhausted; aborting execution\")\n\t\t.withCauseExactlyInstanceOf(IllegalStateException.class)\n\t\t.extracting(Throwable::getSuppressed, array(Throwable[].class))\n\t\t.satisfiesExactly(\n\t\t\tsuppressed1 -> assertThat(suppressed1).isExactlyInstanceOf(IOException.class),\n\t\t\tsuppressed2 -> assertThat(suppressed2).isExactlyInstanceOf(FileNotFoundException.class)\n\t\t);\n```\n\nHaving to combine `extracting(Throwable::getSuppressed, array(Throwable[].class))` with `satisfiesExactly()` seems like it should be unnecessary.\n\nPerhaps I have overlooked something, but I didn't find a simpler way to achieve my goal.\n\nIf there's an easier way to achieve, feel free to point me to that and close this issue.\n\n## Proposal\n\nIt would be nice to introduce something similar to the following in `ThrowableAssertAlternative` (and related classes).\n\n- `withSuppressedExceptionsSatisfying(ThrowingConsumer<? super Throwable>...)`\n- `withSuppressedExceptionsSatisfyingExactly(ThrowingConsumer<? super Throwable>...)`\n\nThat would allow me to simplify my assertion as follows.\n\n```java\nassertThatExceptionOfType(RetryException.class)\n\t\t.isThrownBy(() -> retryTemplate.execute(retryable))\n\t\t.withMessage(\"Retry policy for operation 'test' exhausted; aborting execution\")\n\t\t.withCauseExactlyInstanceOf(IllegalStateException.class)\n\t\t.withSuppressedExceptionsSatisfyingExactly(\n\t\t\tsuppressed1 -> assertThat(suppressed1).isExactlyInstanceOf(IOException.class),\n\t\t\tsuppressed2 -> assertThat(suppressed2).isExactlyInstanceOf(FileNotFoundException.class)\n\t\t);\n```\n\n## Related Issues\n\n- #454\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/3858/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/3858/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]